<td id="06315D94FFAF0014F95DFD3EF7D8FD3F" box="[1727,2051,641,660]" gridcol="5" gridrow="1" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Perennial, erect to ascending</td>
</tr>
<tr id="45E034E8FFAF0014FF72FD0FF7D8FD68" box="[144,2051,688,707]" gridrow="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<th id="06315D94FFAF0014FF72FD0FFEC0FD68" box="[144,283,688,707]" gridcol="0" gridrow="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Stems</th>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FED0FD0FFD59FD68" box="[306,642,688,707]" gridcol="1" gridrow="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Shorter than largest leaves</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FD70FD0FFC33FD68" box="[658,1000,688,707]" gridcol="2" gridrow="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Larger than largest leaves</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FC1AFD0FFA9DFD68" box="[1016,1350,688,707]" gridcol="3" gridrow="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Larger than largest leaves</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FABFFD0FF971FD68" box="[1373,1706,688,707]" gridcol="4" gridrow="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Larger than largest leaves</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014F95DFD0FF7D8FD68" box="[1727,2051,688,707]" gridcol="5" gridrow="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Larger than largest leaves</td>
</tr>
<tr id="45E034E8FFAF0014FF72FD5DF7D8FCE6" box="[144,2051,738,845]" gridrow="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<th id="06315D94FFAF0014FF72FD5DFEC0FCE6" box="[144,283,738,845]" gridcol="0" gridrow="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Stem and foliage pubescence</th>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FED0FD5DFD59FCE6" box="[306,642,738,845]" gridcol="1" gridrow="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pilose, sometimes canescent, simple, two types, short and long trichomes, spreading–ascending, forwardly appressed, rarely retrorse</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FD70FD5DFC33FCE6" box="[658,1000,738,845]" gridcol="2" gridrow="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">One type, simple, pilose to hispidulous with horizontal to retrosely spreading trichomes</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FC1AFD5DFA9DFCE6" box="[1016,1350,738,845]" gridcol="3" gridrow="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">One type, strigulose, trichomes appressed or subappressed, ascending</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FABFFD5DF971FCE6" box="[1373,1706,738,845]" gridcol="4" gridrow="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Cinerous, silvery canescent to silky canescent, ascending</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014F95DFD5DF7D8FCE6" box="[1727,2051,738,845]" gridcol="5" gridrow="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Densely white–villous, spreading, on times retrorse</td>
</tr>
<tr id="45E034E8FFAF0014FF72FCD2F7D8FC36" box="[144,2051,877,925]" gridrow="4" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<th id="06315D94FFAF0014FF72FCD2FEC0FC36" box="[144,283,877,925]" gridcol="0" gridrow="4" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Stipules</th>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FED0FCD2FD59FC36" box="[306,642,877,925]" gridcol="1" gridrow="4" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Semi–amplexicaul</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FD70FCD2FC33FC36" box="[658,1000,877,925]" gridcol="2" gridrow="4" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Dimorphic, the basal ones connate, the upper ones free</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FC1AFCD2FA9DFC36" box="[1016,1350,877,925]" gridcol="3" gridrow="4" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Dimorphic, the basal ones connate, the median and upper ones amplexicaul</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FABFFCD2F971FC36" box="[1373,1706,877,925]" gridcol="4" gridrow="4" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Semi to fully amplexicaul, or free</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014F95DFCD2F7D8FC36" box="[1727,2051,877,925]" gridcol="5" gridrow="4" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Free</td>
</tr>
<tr id="45E034E8FFAF0014FF72FC05F7D8FBAC" box="[144,2051,954,1031]" gridrow="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<th id="06315D94FFAF0014FF72FC05FEC0FBAC" box="[144,283,954,1031]" gridcol="0" gridrow="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Leaflets</th>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FED0FC05FD59FBAC" box="[306,642,954,1031]" gridcol="1" gridrow="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Suborbicular, thick texture, its size diminishing upward along the rachis</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FD70FC05FC33FBAC" box="[658,1000,954,1031]" gridcol="2" gridrow="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Obovate to oblong, retuse, thin textured</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FC1AFC05FA9DFBAC" box="[1016,1350,954,1031]" gridcol="3" gridrow="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Oblanceolate or linear–oblanceolate, obtuse or retuse, thick texture</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FABFFC05F971FBAC" box="[1373,1706,954,1031]" gridcol="4" gridrow="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Obovate, broad–elliptic, rhombic–ovate to suborbicular, retuse, thick texture</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014F95DFC05F7D8FBAC" box="[1727,2051,954,1031]" gridcol="5" gridrow="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Elliptic, elliptic–obovate to obovate, retuse, thick texture, its size diminishing upward along the rachis</td>
</tr>
<tr id="45E034E8FFAF0014FF72FB9CF7D8FB9D" box="[144,2051,1059,1078]" gridrow="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<th id="06315D94FFAF0014FF72FB9CFEC0FB9D" box="[144,283,1059,1078]" gridcol="0" gridrow="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Peduncles</th>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FED0FB9CFD59FB9D" box="[306,642,1059,1078]" gridcol="1" gridrow="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Prostrate to reclinate in fruit</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FD70FB9CFC33FB9D" box="[658,1000,1059,1078]" gridcol="2" gridrow="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Spreading or incurved</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FC1AFB9CFA9DFB9D" box="[1016,1350,1059,1078]" gridcol="3" gridrow="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Divaricate to incurved–ascending</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FABFFB9CF971FB9D" box="[1373,1706,1059,1078]" gridcol="4" gridrow="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Erect to slightly incurved, ascending</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014F95DFB9CF7D8FB9D" box="[1727,2051,1059,1078]" gridcol="5" gridrow="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Erect, incurved ascending</td>
</tr>
<tr id="45E034E8FFAF0014FF72FBEDF7D8FBCE" box="[144,2051,1106,1125]" gridrow="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<th id="06315D94FFAF0014FF72FBEDFEC0FBCE" box="[144,283,1106,1125]" gridcol="0" gridrow="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pedicels</th>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FED0FBEDFD59FBCE" box="[306,642,1106,1125]" gridcol="1" gridrow="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Persistent</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FD70FBEDFC33FBCE" box="[658,1000,1106,1125]" gridcol="2" gridrow="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Persistent</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FC1AFBEDFA9DFBCE" box="[1016,1350,1106,1125]" gridcol="3" gridrow="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Persistent</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FABFFBEDF971FBCE" box="[1373,1706,1106,1125]" gridcol="4" gridrow="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Persistent</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014F95DFBEDF7D8FBCE" box="[1727,2051,1106,1125]" gridcol="5" gridrow="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Caducous</td>
</tr>
<tr id="45E034E8FFAF0014FF72FB3DF7D8FB19" box="[144,2051,1154,1202]" gridrow="8" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<th id="06315D94FFAF0014FF72FB3DFEC0FB19" box="[144,283,1154,1202]" gridcol="0" gridrow="8" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Calyx shape</th>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FED0FB3DFD59FB19" box="[306,642,1154,1202]" gridcol="1" gridrow="8" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Cylindric to deeply campanulate,</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FD70FB3DFC33FB19" box="[658,1000,1154,1202]" gridcol="2" gridrow="8" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Campanulate</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FC1AFB3DFA9DFB19" box="[1016,1350,1154,1202]" gridcol="3" gridrow="8" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Cylindric to cylndro–campanulate</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FABFFB3DF971FB19" box="[1373,1706,1154,1202]" gridcol="4" gridrow="8" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Campanulate</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014F95DFB3DF7D8FB19" box="[1727,2051,1154,1202]" gridcol="5" gridrow="8" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Suboblong–urceolate to subglobose– urceolate</td>
</tr>
<tr id="45E034E8FFAF0014FF72FB6FF7D8FAAB" box="[144,2051,1232,1280]" gridrow="9" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<th id="06315D94FFAF0014FF72FB6FFEC0FAAB" box="[144,283,1232,1280]" gridcol="0" gridrow="9" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Calyx-tube shape</th>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FED0FB6FFD59FAAB" box="[306,642,1232,1280]" gridcol="1" gridrow="9" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Usually constricted upward, broadest below the middle</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FD70FB6FFC33FAAB" box="[658,1000,1232,1280]" gridcol="2" gridrow="9" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Campanulate, not constricted upward</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FC1AFB6FFA9DFAAB" box="[1016,1350,1232,1280]" gridcol="3" gridrow="9" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Cylndric–campanulate, not constricted upward</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FABFFB6FF971FAAB" box="[1373,1706,1232,1280]" gridcol="4" gridrow="9" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Campanulate, not constricted upward</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014F95DFB6FF7D8FAAB" box="[1727,2051,1232,1280]" gridcol="5" gridrow="9" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Urceolate,</td>
</tr>
<tr id="45E034E8FFAF0014FF72FA9BF7D8FAFE" box="[144,2051,1316,1365]" gridrow="10" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<th id="06315D94FFAF0014FF72FA9BFEC0FAFE" box="[144,283,1316,1365]" gridcol="0" gridrow="10" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Flowers color</th>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FED0FA9BFD59FAFE" box="[306,642,1316,1365]" gridcol="1" gridrow="10" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pink–purple, pink–lavender, to yellowish with lilac, or creamy–white</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FD70FA9BFC33FAFE" box="[658,1000,1316,1365]" gridcol="2" gridrow="10" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pale purple, ochroleucous (when dry)</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FC1AFA9BFA9DFAFE" box="[1016,1350,1316,1365]" gridcol="3" gridrow="10" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Purple to pink–purple</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FABFFA9BF971FAFE" box="[1373,1706,1316,1365]" gridcol="4" gridrow="10" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pink, pink–purple</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014F95DFA9BF7D8FAFE" box="[1727,2051,1316,1365]" gridcol="5" gridrow="10" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Petals blue to blue–violet and basally white</td>
</tr>
<tr id="45E034E8FFAF0014FF72FAC9F7D8FA22" box="[144,2051,1398,1417]" gridrow="11" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<th id="06315D94FFAF0014FF72FAC9FEC0FA22" box="[144,283,1398,1417]" gridcol="0" gridrow="11" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Banner size</th>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FED0FAC9FD59FA22" box="[306,642,1398,1417]" gridcol="1" gridrow="11" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">12–24.5 mm long</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FD70FAC9FC33FA22" box="[658,1000,1398,1417]" gridcol="2" gridrow="11" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">7.2–10 mm long</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FC1AFAC9FA9DFA22" box="[1016,1350,1398,1417]" gridcol="3" gridrow="11" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">13–17 mm long</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FABFFAC9F971FA22" box="[1373,1706,1398,1417]" gridcol="4" gridrow="11" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">13.2–18 mm long</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014F95DFAC9F7D8FA22" box="[1727,2051,1398,1417]" gridcol="5" gridrow="11" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">14–16 mm long</td>
</tr>
<tr id="45E034E8FFAF0014FF72FA10F7D8F93B" box="[144,2051,1455,1680]" gridrow="12" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<th id="06315D94FFAF0014FF72FA10FEC0F93B" box="[144,283,1455,1680]" gridcol="0" gridrow="12" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pods</th>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FED0FA10FD59F93B" box="[306,642,1455,1680]" gridcol="1" gridrow="12" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Humistrate, ovate, elliptic, lunate to linear–oblong, 9-25 mm long, inflated but never bladdery, contracted distally into a short beak, valves, stiffly papery, leathery to subligneous, with a complete septum. Not concealed by the calyx</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FD70FA10FC33F93B" box="[658,1000,1455,1680]" gridcol="2" gridrow="12" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Spreading ascending to declined, sessile to short stipitate (2–3 mm), 10-18 mm long, strongly compressed triquetrous, oblong, valves papery, with a complete septum. Not concealed by the calyx</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FC1AFA10FA9DF93B" box="[1016,1350,1455,1680]" gridcol="3" gridrow="12" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Erect, sessile or with stipe-like up to 1 mm long, 12-24 mm long, obliquely ovoid to ellipsoid, turgid to inflated, deltoid or acuminate distally, 1.2–2.4 cm long, slightly compressed, valves stiffly papery or leathery black or white–strigulose with a complete septum. Not concealed by the calyx</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FABFFA10F971F93B" box="[1373,1706,1455,1680]" gridcol="4" gridrow="12" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">pod narrowly to broadly ovate– acumminate or oblong, slightly or greatly inflated, 12–22 mm long, incurved, contracted distally into a triangular beak, valves papery, glabrous or minute pubescent, with a complete septum. Not concealed by the calyx</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014F95DFA10F7D8F93B" box="[1727,2051,1455,1680]" gridcol="5" gridrow="12" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Elliptic to suboblong, tumescent, leathery slightly compressed laterally, abruptly contracted at the apex, 6–8 mm long. Complete septum. Concealed by the calyx</td>
</tr>
<tr id="45E034E8FFAF0014FF72F906F7D8F967" box="[144,2051,1721,1740]" gridrow="13" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<th id="06315D94FFAF0014FF72F906FEC0F967" box="[144,283,1721,1740]" gridcol="0" gridrow="13" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Ovules</th>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FED0F906FD59F967" box="[306,642,1721,1740]" gridcol="1" gridrow="13" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">20–31</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FD70F906FC33F967" box="[658,1000,1721,1740]" gridcol="2" gridrow="13" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">9–18</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FC1AF906FA9DF967" box="[1016,1350,1721,1740]" gridcol="3" gridrow="13" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">20–30</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014FABFF906F971F967" box="[1373,1706,1721,1740]" gridcol="4" gridrow="13" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">18–22</td>
<td id="06315D94FFAF0014F95DF906F7D8F967" box="[1727,2051,1721,1740]" gridcol="5" gridrow="13" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">4</td>
</tr>
</table>
</paragraph>
<subSubSection id="B3CA6521FFA8FFEFFF5FFF21FC56FF77" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FB6F36AAFFA8FFEFFF5FFF21FC56FF77" blockId="4.[136,1451,158,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis id="C9A4EAB8FFA8FFEFFF5FFF21FEBFFF13" bold="true" box="[189,356,158,184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Etymology:—</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName id="3CD04D29FFA8FFEFFE37FF20FDEAFF13" box="[469,561,159,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Astragalus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rupertii">
<emphasis id="C9A4EAB8FFA8FFEFFE37FF20FDEAFF13" box="[469,561,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Rupertii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of this new section is in honor to Rupert Charles Barneby (1911–2000), specialist and author of the monumental work of 
<taxonomicName id="3CD04D29FFA8FFEFFDDDFF7DFD63FF77" box="[575,696,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Astragalus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C9A4EAB8FFA8FFEFFDDDFF7DFD63FF77" box="[575,696,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Astragalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of North America.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B3CA6521FFA8FFEFFF5FFF59FC34FE8F" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FB6F36AAFFA8FFEFFF5FFF59FC34FE8F" blockId="4.[136,1451,158,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
The next dichotomous key is added to recognize and differentiate this new section from the other ones that grouped species in 
<collectingCountry id="83C7763AFFA8FFEFFEBDFEB5FE6EFE8F" box="[351,437,266,292]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(adapted from 
<bibRefCitation id="9F414B5BFFA8FFEFFD83FEB5FCD9FE8F" author="Barneby, R. C." box="[609,770,266,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" pagination="1 - 1188" refId="ref5365" refString="Barneby, R. C. (1964) Atlas of North American Astragalus. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 13: 1 - 1188." type="journal article" year="1964">Barneby 1964</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9F414B5BFFA8FFEFFCEFFEB5FC3FFE8F" author="Estrada, C. E. &amp; Villarreal, Q. J. &amp; Encina, D. J." box="[781,996,266,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" pagination="163 - 172" refId="ref5624" refString="Estrada, C. E., Villarreal, Q. J. &amp; Encina, D. J. (2020) A new species and a new section of Astragalus (Fabaceae: Papilionoideae) from Mexico. Phytotaxa 428 (3): 163 - 172. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 428.3.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Estrada 
<emphasis id="C9A4EAB8FFA8FFEFFC8AFEB4FC7BFE8F" box="[872,928,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
